# Project: Trinity New Zealand Immigration Services — Marketing Website

## Overview
Single-page marketing website for Trinity New Zealand Immigration Services Ltd.
Built with React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS. Deployed on Netlify.

## Tech Stack
- React 18 with TypeScript (strict mode)
- Vite 8 as build tool (build command: `npm run build`, output: `dist/`)
- Tailwind CSS v3 for all styling — do NOT write custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- React Router DOM v7 for routing
- Netlify for hosting, forms, and deployment
- Node.js >= 20.19.0

## Project Structure
- `src/content/site.ts` — ALL editable copy, links, and site metadata lives here. Always update content here, not inline in components.
- `src/` — React components and pages
- `public/` — static assets
- `index.html` — contains hidden Netlify form for static form detection at deploy time

## Code Style Rules
- Always use TypeScript. No plain `.js` files in `src/`.
- Use functional components with hooks only. No class components.
- Use Tailwind utility classes for all styling. No inline styles, no separate CSS files.
- Keep components small and focused. Split into smaller components if a file exceeds ~100 lines.
- Use descriptive, readable variable and function names.
- Add brief comments for any logic that isn't immediately obvious.

## Netlify-Specific Rules
- The contact form uses Netlify Forms. Always keep the hidden static form in `index.html` in sync with the visible React form fields.
- Form submissions POST to `/` with `application/x-www-form-urlencoded`. Do not change this.
- Do not add a backend or serverless functions unless explicitly asked.
- HTTPS and SSL are handled automatically by Netlify — do not add any certificate logic.

## Content Rules
- All visa and immigration information must reference official Immigration New Zealand (INZ) pathways (e.g. AEWV, NZeTA, Green List, SMC).
- Always include a disclaimer pointing users to INZ for authoritative and up-to-date requirements.
- Do not invent or assume visa criteria — flag any uncertain content for human review.
- Tone should be professional, clear, and trustworthy — this is a licensed immigration services business.

## Do NOT Do These
- Do not install new npm packages without being asked.
- Do not switch from Tailwind to any other CSS framework.
- Do not add analytics scripts (e.g. Google Analytics) unless explicitly asked.
- Do not modify `netlify.toml` unless asked.
- Do not add `console.log` statements to production code.
- Do not use `any` type in TypeScript — always type properly.
